FBIS3-7242 "dreas059__a94024" FBIS-EAS-94-059-A Document Type:Daily Report 25 Mar 1994 ANNEX Japan SDPJ Grapples With DPRK Nuclear Issue Concerned With WPK Ties OW2503124794 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 25 Mar 94 Morning Edition p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW2503124794 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN Language: Japanese Article Type:BFN [Text] Speaking at a meeting of Dietmen on 24 March, Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ] Chairman Murayama touched on the issue of the DPRK's rejection of nuclear inspections. He said: "The party has to keep its friendly relations with the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK]. However, as a member of the ruling parties, we have to study what the party can do." In this way, he disclosed a plan to fully study what the party should do, including the possibility of holding talks with the WPK.
